The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 THE DVD 

 (MusicWorld, Rs 595)

 December 8 marks the 25th death anniversary of John Lennon, and what better way to remember the legend than through this look at the making of his classic album, Imagine? Also, glimpses of John amp; Yoko?s celebrity lifestyle and interview footage. 

 THE DISPLAY 

 (Gaganendra Pradarshashala, 2 pm-8 pm, December 7 to 13)

 The exhibition, ?From an imperial product to a national drink?, will feature calendars, illustrations, cartoons, photographs, paintings and other materials. Organised by Centre for Studies in Social Sciences in association with Tea Board India. 

 THE FILMS

 (December 9 and 10, Max Mueller Bhavan)

 The bunch of films directed by Truffaut to be shown on Dec 9 are Two English Girls at 2 pm, The Woman Next Door at 4.30 pm, The 400 Blows at 6.30 pm, and Jules and Jim at 8.30 pm. On Dec 10, The Soft Skin at 1.30 pm, Stolen Kisses at 4 pm, Bed and Board at 6 pm, Love on the Run at 8 pm and The Last Metro at 10 pm. Hosted by The French Association.




